# model 

<button class = 'btn btn-primary' data-bs-toggle='modal' data-bs-target = '#modal'> open </button>
// we have data-bs-toggle to chooose what to happen
// data-bs-target = selector to chose on what we want effect on. this is needed to be more specific. 

<div class = 'modal fade' class = 'modal'> // modal-xl 
    <div class = 'modal-dialog'>  // modal-dialog-centered modal-diaglog-scrollable modal-fullscreen
        <div class = 'modal-content'>
            .modeal-header
                <button class = 'btn-close' data-bs-dismiss = 'modal' data-bs-target = '#modal'>
            .modal-body 
            .modal-footer 
                <button class = 'btn btn-primary' data-bs-dismiss = 'modal'> close </button>

# collapse 

allows us to show and hide some components 

toggle type = collapse
and target = selector of component to collapse

<button class = 'btn btn-primary' data-bs-toggle = 'collapse' data-bs-target = '#row' aria-expanded = 'true' area-control='row'>

<div class = 'row show'> // row should already know it's expanded or collapsed add collapse/show class 
    <div class = 'col'>
        <div class = 'box'> </div>
    </div>
</div>

## if many elements shares same selector, we can collapse all them with single button


# navbar 

<nav class = 'navbar navbar-expand'> -- full screen navbar. 
    <div class = "continaer">
        <a href = "#" class = 'navbar-brand'> brand </a>
        <ul class = 'navbar-nav'>
            <li class = 'nav-item'>
                <a href = '#' class = 'nav-link active' area-page='current'> </a>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <div class = 'navbar-text'> random text </div> 
    </div>
</nav> 


like this we can create navbar with ICON and ITEMS, which can have active class to show it differently. 
        ** area page just set for active page. 
    
nav-link === active/disabled etc... 


## coloring navbar
    background = bg-dark 
    then we can also set navbar coloring for dark using 
    navbar-dark. 

## collapsing navbar 
if we remove navbar-expanded it's going to be shown in collapsed manner 
let's say we only want it expanded on md and above 
use  .navbar-expand-md

whole navbar-nav needed to be under collapse 

<button class = 'navbar-toggler' data-bs-toggle = 'collapse' data-bs-target = '#nav' area-controls = 'nav' area-label = 'expanded nav'>
    <span class = 'navbar-toggler-icon'>   </span>
<buttton>
<div class = 'navbar-collapse collapse' id = 'nav'>
    <ul class = 'navbar-nav'>
        ...
    </ul>
</div>

then going md and below auto hides navbar

